Disconnect an Omnichannel Inventory Connection

You can delete a connection to Omnichannel Inventory if you don’t need it. Removing the connection stops Data Cloud from using your inventory as a data source and data action target.

REQUIRED EDITIONS AND USER PERMISSIONS
Available in: Lightning Experience


USER PERMISSIONS NEEDED
To disconnect Omnichannel Inventory:	Data Cloud Admin permission set OR Commerce Intelligence Admin permission set
NOTE Disconnecting deletes the data streams and associated data action targets for this connection. This action can’t be undone.
From Data Cloud Setup, in the Quick Find box, enter Omnichannel Inventory Connector, and then select Omnichannel Inventory Connector.
Find the connector that you want to disconnect.
From the dropdown menu next to the connection name, select Disconnect.
Click Disconnect.

The connector is removed from the list of connected Omnichannel Inventory instances.
